m suitability.\n\nReliability: B is 100% reliable. D takes responsibility seriously (good). A? not mentioned. C? not mentioned.\n\nTechnical competence: A has excellent spatial vision, sees complex connections (good for navigation). B has excellent computer skills, good at assessing weather (technical). C makes correct decisions quickly (cognitive). D solves problems extremely well, concentrates, responds to unexpected events (technical). All have some.\n\nCalm under pressure: B keeps calm in crisis. C handles stress well. D responds adequately to unexpected events. A? not mentioned.\n\nTeamwork/communication: A has leadership qualities but poor at taking criticism, unorganized. B can be uncooperative, grumpy. C creates positive atmosphere, but difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric. D regarded as arrogant, weak leadership.\n\nLong-term suitability: B reliable, but uncooperative may affect crew. C not willing to further education (bad for development). D weak leadership, arrogance may hinder. A unorganized, poor at criticism.\n\nWe need to pick best overall. Likely B has strong reliability, calm, technical (weather, computer). Weaknesses are attitude (grumpy, uncooperative) which could affect teamwork. But maybe still best? C has good stress handling and crew atmosphere but communication issues and egocentric, not willing to develop. D strong problem solving, responsibility, but arrogance and weak leadership. A strong anticipation, leadership, but unorganized and poor at criticism.\n\nConsidering long-distance flights require high reliability, calm, technical, and teamwork. B's reliability and calm are top. Weaknesses may be mitigated? But we must not mitigate; we weigh as evidence. Uncooperative could be serious. However, other candidates have more severe teamwork issues (egocentric, arrogance, weak leadership). B's uncooperativeness is a weakness but maybe less severe than arrogance? Hard.\n\nWe could ask other agents for missing info: maybe about candidate D's leadership or candidate A's reliability. But we have all attributes. So we can decide.\n\nI think B is best overall despite attitude issues because reliability and calm are critical. So vote for Candidate B.\n\nNow produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE summarizing reasoning."}
